ld celery, has been used in traditional medicine for its various health benefits. It is believed to have anti-inflammatory and antiseptic properties, which can help to soothe skin irritations and wounds. Additionally, the plant's extracts may have antioxidant effects, which can help to protect against cell damage and promote overall well-being. Some studies suggest that Selinum galbanum may also have anti-cancer properties, although more research is needed to confirm this. The plant's essential oils have been used to aid digestion and relieve symptoms of indigestion and bloating.", "parts": "Selinum galbanum is a plant that is used in traditional medicine. The medicinal parts of Selinum galbanum are the roots and leaves, which are used for their antiseptic and anti-inflammatory properties. The plant has been used to treat various health conditions, including fever, rheumatism, and digestive problems. The roots of the plant are said to be particularly effective in treating fever and rheumatism. In addition, the leaves of Selinum galbanum are used to make a tea that is used to treat digestive problems."}